RautSoft.math.nlp
Class DonlpJava

java.lang.Object
  RautSoft.math.nlp.DonlpJava

public class DonlpJava
extends java.lang.Object

DonlpJava is written by Dr. Lakshmi K. Raut as a Java JNI interface to Dr. Peter Spellucci's C implementation of donlp2. DonlpJava class has the following methods the ones with a zero at the end means the functions. and the vector x all are indexed from 0.

  • NlpUnConstrainedNumerical() or NlpUnConstrainedNumerical0()
  • NlpMixedConstrainedNumerical() or NlpMixedConstrainedNumerical0()
  • NlpBoundConstrainedNumerical() 
     
                 Min f(x)
                 subject to
                           xl < x   < xu
                           bl < Ax  < bu
                           cl < g(x) < cu
    Problem dimension
  • nJ = dim(x),
  • nlinJ = number of linear constraints
  • nonlinJ = number of nonlinear constraints ,
  • itermaJ = number of iterative steps allowed ,
  • nstepJ = number of tries in the backtracking allowed
  • analytJ = False means numerical derivatives for gradients. Presently this option only works.
  • x0 is an initial vector of dimension 1+nJ, the first element corresponding to index 0 should be set to 0 for the first set of methods
  • xLow and xUp vectors in the main program should be of dimension 1+nJ+nlin+nonlin and follow that order, again the dimension is one less for the second set of methods. the first element of x0 and xLow and xUp are never used canbe always set to 0.
